Thousands of people have been evacuated from La Palma in the Canary Islands after a volcanic eruption.

Dramatic aerial footage showed lava from the Cumbre Vieja volcano spilling downhill and destroying several houses.

#Volcano #CanaryIslands #BBCNews

node.title: Cumbre Vieja volcano erupts in Canary Islands

node.text:
Netflix's royal drama The Crown and Apple TV comedy Ted Lasso were the big winners at Sunday's Emmy Awards.

The Crown's prizes included best drama series and four acting wins - for Gillian Anderson, Olivia Colman, Josh O'Connor and Tobias Menzies.

Tap the link in our bio to read all of the winners on the night.

#BBCNews

node.title: The Crown and Ted Lasso sweep Emmy Awards 2021

node.text:
They were supposed to be the face of Afghanistan's future - female cabin crew working for the national carrier, Ariana Airlines.

Now, they have been told not to come back to work for the time being by their new bosses, the Taliban.

Eleven of the women have come together to hide in an abandoned house, out of fear for their future. Our chief international correspondent Lyse Doucet went to meet them.

#Afghanistan #BBCNews

"We have gone through many difficult days."

The only female whirling dancer in Afghanistan was about to start her biggest tour around the country. Then the Taliban took control.

The group sees Sufi whirling dervishes as against Islamic law so Fahima Mirzaei had no choice but to run. This is the story of her escape from her homeland.

#Afghanistan #Dancing #BBCNews

node.title: The escape of the whirling dancer

"The more attention you pay it, the more it consumes your life and I don't want to consume my life."

Tom Parker from boy band The Wanted says he refuses to let cancer dominate his life, almost a year on from being diagnosed with an inoperable brain tumour. 

Tap the link in our bio to read more about the fundraiser he is planning at the Royal Albert Hall in London which will feature Ed Sheeran, Liam Payne and McFly as well as the first appearance for more than seven years by The Wanted.

Dr Bnar Talabani is the only doctor from Wales on Team Halo, a UN-backed group of doctors and scientists using social media to dispel vaccine misinformation.

node.text:
Sixty three endangered African penguins have been killed by a swarm of bees in a rare event near Cape Town. 

The protected birds, from a colony in Simonstown, were found on the shore with multiple bee-stings and no other injuries, conservationists said.

This was the first known attack at the world-famous Boulders Beach, which attracts up to 60,000 visitors a year.

"Usually the penguins and bees co-exist," said Dr Alison Kock, a marine biologist with South Africa's national parks agency (SANParks).

"The bees don't sting unless provoked - we are working on the assumption that a nest or hive in the area was disturbed and caused a mass of bees to flee the nest, swarm and became aggressive," she added. 

For more on what the scientists think happened, click the link in our bio.

#BBCNews #penguins #nature

node.text:
Riot police were deployed as hundreds of people protested against mandatory vaccinations in Australia.

Officers reportedly used rubber bullets and pepper spray, after violent crowds damaged property and set off flares in the streets of Melbourne.

The protests followed an announcement that construction workers will be required to show proof that they have had at least one vaccine dose in order to continue to work.

Australia has been praised for its relatively low Covid-19 death rate, however, about half the population has recently been placed in lockdown due to outbreaks in the cities of Melbourne, Sydney and Canberra, with the Delta variant causing cases to rise more rapidly.

Tap the link in our bio to read about Australia's fight against Covid.

(📷 Getty Images, EPA)

#Australia #Coronavirus #BBCNews

The G7 members were shown around by Sir Lindsay Hoyle, the UK’s Speaker of the House of Commons, who said TV shows can help counter hate and can influence people's viewpoints.

Nancy Pelosi, speaker of the US House of Representatives, was among those hearing about the soap's impact.

The G7 (Group of Seven) is an organisation of the world's seven largest so-called advanced economies. They are Canada, France, Germany, Italy, Japan, the UK and the United States.

Umeno Sumiyama and Koume Kodama have broken the record set by late Japanese twin sisters Kin Narita and Gin Kanie to become the world's oldest living identical twins.

The sisters, both described as sociable people, were born on 5 November 1913 in Shodoshima.

As a Covid precaution, the twins - who live in different parts of Japan - were presented their official certificates celebrating their achievement by staff at their separate care homes.

In Japan, life expectancy is the highest in the world, and older people command considerable respect.

The oldest living person on record, according to Guinness, is 118-year-old Japanese woman Kane Tanaka.

Click the link in our bio to find out how old the twins were who previously held the record.

(📷 Guinness World Records)

node.text:
The US is relaxing its Covid travel restrictions, ending an 18-month ban on UK and EU passengers.

From November, passengers will be allowed to travel to the US if they are fully vaccinated and undergo testing and contact tracing, the White House said. Donald Trump introduced the travel ban in March 2020 at the beginning of the pandemic.

White House Covid-19 coordinator Jeff Zients announced the "new international air travel system" on Monday, explaining that the country would be opening up to fully vaccinated passengers.

Tap the link in our bio for more on the lifting of restriction and the new requirements for entering the US.

(📷 EPA)

#BBCNews

node.text:
The Queen is “delighted” that her granddaughter Princess Beatrice has given birth to her first child, Buckingham Palace has said. 

The princess and her husband Edoardo Mapelli Mozzi have welcomed a baby girl, weighing 6lb 2oz, who was born on Saturday.

The baby girl will be 11th in line to the throne and is the Queen's 12th great-grandchild.

A statement from Buckingham Palace said: "The new baby's grandparents and great-grandparents have all been informed and are delighted with the news. The family would like to thank all the staff at the hospital for their wonderful care."

Tap the link in our bio for more on the reaction to the news.

(📷 EPA, Reuters)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by BBC News on September 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'BBC NEWS Female chess icon sues Netflix over Queen's Gambit portrayal'.

node.text:
A Georgian chess icon has filed a defamation lawsuit against Netflix, saying she was incorrectly portrayed in the hit series The Queen's Gambit.

The case refers to a sequence in the drama's final episode which says Nona Gaprindashvili, now 80, had never played competitive chess with men.

In the final episode, a commentator mentions Gaprindashvili when describing fictional lead character Beth Harmon: "The only unusual thing about her, really, is her sex. And even that's not unique in Russia. There's Nona Gaprindashvili, but she's the female world champion and has never faced men."

The document says that by 1968, the year in which the episode is set, she had faced at least 59 male players.

The 25-page case filed in the Federal District Court in Los Angeles said: "Netflix brazenly and deliberately lied about Gaprindashvili's achievements for the cheap and cynical purpose of 'heightening the drama' by making it appear that its fictional hero had managed to do what no other woman, including Gaprindashvili, had done."

Tap the link in our bio for more on the case and why Netflix has dismissed it as having "no merit".
